comments: Simons (POR) hand gets caught briefly in Towns' (MIN) jersey and marginal contact occurs as he disengages on the defensive switch.
Simons (POR) places a resting hand to Vanderbilt's (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his dunk attempt at the basket.
Towns (MIN) moves alongside of Lillard (POR) and marginal contact occurs as they come together at the start of the drive.
Edwards (MIN) maintains a legal guarding position on Powell (POR) during the drive before his errant pass.
Russell (MIN) is in the paint for about three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Covington (POR) brings his arm down and makes contact to Edwards' (MIN) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (POR) establishes himself in a somewhat wide screening position in Edwards' (MIN) path, and marginal contact occurs as Edwards goes over the pick to maintain his defensive matchup.
Nance Jr. (POR) has his arm extended out and marginal contact occurs with Vanderbilt's (MIN) arm after he secures the rebound, which does not affect his ability to make his intended pass.
Beverley (MIN) reaches in and makes contact with Lillard's (POR) wrist, which causes him to lose control of the ball.
Covington (POR) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Towns (MIN) as he tries to deflect the inbounds pass away.
Towns' (MIN) heel comes down out of bounds before calling timeout.
Nance Jr. (POR) and Towns (MIN) mutually engage and disengage off-ball and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Nance Jr.'s ability to get to the inbounds pass.
Covington (POR) commits a take foul on Russell (MIN).
Covington (POR) releases his inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Nance Jr. (POR) initiates the marginal contact with Towns (MIN) as they engage and disengage during the inbounds.
Simons (POR) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN).
Russell (MIN) grabs and holds Covington's (POR) arm, which affects his FOM.
Simons (POR) commits a take foul on Russell (MIN).

Lillard (POR) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Vanderbilt's (MIN) arm and head as he secures the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
